description:
&lt;p&gt;Have you got a positive approach with a dynamic outlook to change the look of unscheduled care within occupational therapy in adult mental health?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated and enthusiastic band 7 occupational therapist to lead the occupational therapy service in our unscheduled care mental health services in Cardiff and the Vale UHB.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will hold a clinical caseload delivering occupationally focused assessments and interventions. You will also provide professional leadership, including supervision and some operational management, to a small group of occupational therapists. This includes band 6, band 5 and support staff. You will also have responsibility for maintaining a safe working environment in line with Health and Safety legislation, policies and procedures. As a senior member of the occupational therapy team you will lead development of the service within the strategy of occupational therapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiff and Vale provides many opportunities for professional development and has a strong professional network providing supervision and learning opportunities. A commitment to collaborative working with the multi-disciplinary team is essential. We actively support the education of Occupational Therapy students within our service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are searching for someone who shares our values that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We care about the people we serve and the people we work with&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We trust one another&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We respect each other&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We take personal responsibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We treat people with kindness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We act with integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post holders will be expected at all times to behave in accordance with our values demonstrating commitment to the delivery of high quality services to citizens.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica Powell&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Lead Occupational Therapist Mental Health&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hafan y Coed, UHL&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;02921824892&lt;/p&gt;
